[/asy]
Let's think step by step to solve this problemFirst, we need to find the length of the base of the trapezoid. Since the trapezoid is isosceles and inscribed in a semicircle, the two non-parallel sides are radii of the semicircle and have length 1 meter. Let the length of the base be $b$ meters. Then the height of the trapezoid is also 1 meter, since it is the radius of the semicircle.

[asy]
fill((0,10)..(-10,0)--(10,0)..cycle,black);
fill((-10,0)--(-5,8.7)--(5,8.7)--(10,0)--cycle,white);
draw((0,10)..(-10,0)--(10,0)..cycle);
