add(pathticks(a--o, s=3));

[/asy]

solution:
Since $\triangle BDA$ is isosceles, $\angle BAD = \angle ABD = x^\circ$.
Since $\triangle CDA$ is isosceles, $\angle CAD = \angle ACD = y^\circ$. [asy]
import olympiad;
size(7cm);

pair a = dir(76);
pair b = (-1, 0);
pair c = (1, 0);
pair o = (0, 0);

draw(a--b--c--cycle);
draw(a--o);

